    "body" : "In the other direction, it&#39;s woprth remembering that <b><i>the entire raison d&#39;etre</i></b> of Swift is that it is for &quot;protocol oriented programming&quot;.  You do everything with &quot;protocol extensions&quot; in Swift ubiquitously.  For example <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/41796998/protocol-extension-doesnt-seem-to-enforce-variable-in-consumer\">here</a> is a subtle issue about Swift (ie: &quot;about protocol extensions&quot;) which illustrates some of the issues."
