      "body" : "&quot;<i>the protocol&lt;&gt; keyword</i>&quot;: That&#39;s really cool! I think this is what is called an <i>intersection type</i> in the type system theory community. I Java you can only have such types for type parameters with multiple bounds. <a href=\"http://www.cs.rice.edu/~javaplt/papers/oopsla2008.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">This paper</a> suggests introducing them in Java as first class type, with syntax to denote them."
