  "title" : "Compare Protocol in Swift vs Interface in Java",
  "body" : "<p>I'm going through the iOS tutorial from <a href=\"https://developer.apple.com/library/prerelease/ios/referencelibrary/GettingStarted/DevelopiOSAppsSwift/Lesson1.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40015214-CH3-SW1\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Apple developer page</a>.</p>\n\n<p>It seems to me that <code>protocol</code> and <code>interface</code> almost have the same functionality.</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Are there any differences between the two?</p></li>\n<li><p>the different usage in the project?</p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Updated</strong> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Yes</strong>, I did read the link above and I'm still not sure what the differences and usage between <code>protocol</code> and <code>interface</code>. When I ask a question like this, I would like to see a simple explanation about the topic. Sometime it could be tough to get everything from the documentation.</p>\n"
}